Description: Tapering handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine light pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Aristos. The shape of the handle is very clearly much later than the date of the known Rhodian fabricant of this name. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0758)
